  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Thought of this while hashing out #12823.\n\nLuckily, pod resources are not yet updatable #5774.\n\nHowever, they are in pod templates.\n\nScenario: User sets limits in ReplicationController template. Later, user does a get, modifies limits, and then put. They changed limit but not request. Boom.\n\nMy proposal is that we don't default request from limit in pod templates and that we just do it in pods. LimitRange also just applies to pods. The fields are not updatable in pods, so not a problem there.\n\nI'm sure what the best way is to handle this in the defaulting pass. We might need to copy the Go struct type for ResourceRequirements.\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/api/v1/defaults.go#L168\n\ncc @davidopp @derekwaynecarr @vishh \n",
